The paper deals with the analysis of the weight spectrum and stopping set size spectrum of a class of generalized low-density parity-check (GLDPC) codes, which are commonly studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of the growth rate or spectral shape of these spectra, which is a topic of interest in functional analysis (cs.FA). The analysis involves the use of certain symmetry properties, which is a common theme in the study of discrete structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of certain statistical techniques to analyze the local weight distribution, which is a topic of interest in the field of statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the study of the performance of these codes, which is a topic of interest in the field of network information theory (cs.NI).
